# Capability signature as typed observation vector

**IF:** a mission has hinge-log evidence across multiple hinges.
**HOWEVER:** raw tag-activation counts measure recording cadence, not capability development — normalise by baseline frequency (M-learning-loop checkpoint-1, articulation-floor noise).
**THEN:** produce a typed feature map: {capability-dimension × {channel × confidence}} per mission, so cross-mission scoring is comparable without collapsing into prose interpretation.
**BECAUSE:** the structured-observation-vector pattern applied at the cross-mission mining scale — a capability signature is a typed observation, not a narrative description.
**NEXT-STEPS:** the four channels (pattern / vocabulary / connection / question) tag each capability dimension; confidence is per-tag (strong/weak/baseline) so weak-tag activations are distinguishable from strong ones.
